class Solution {
    public String sortString(String s) {
        int[] freq = new int[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        int n = s.length();
        while (sb.length() < n) {
            for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
                if (freq[i] > 0) {
                    sb.append((char) (i + 'a'));
                    freq[i]--;
                }
            }
            for (int i = 25; i >= 0; i--) {
                if (freq[i] > 0) {
                    sb.append((char) (i + 'a'));
                    freq[i]--;
                }
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a frequency array to count occurrences of each letter. Constructs the result by alternately appending the smallest remaining and then largest remaining letters in ascending and descending passes. Runs in linear time relative to string length and uses constant extra space.

